parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including the loss of power, faulty gauges, and reduced engine power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing issues with the gauges
lights
and engine power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate or stuck readings on the gauges, including the speedometer, fuel gauge, and oil pressure gauge, which can lead to accidents or safety issues.
symptoms: The gauges on the instrument cluster become stuck or provide inaccurate readings
including the speedometer
fuel gauge
and oil pressure gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to slow down or stall, leading to accidents or safety issues, especially on highways.
symptoms: The "Reduced Engine Power" warning light comes on
and the vehicle's speed is reduced
often without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keychain and alarm system can cause the vehicle to shut down or become stuck, leading to safety issues or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The keychain and alarm system malfunction
causing the vehicle to shut down or become stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause sudden and complete loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
brake fluid leaks from the lines
and the vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle's power steering system fails
causing the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up
resulting in a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Intermediate Shaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and intermediate shaft can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering column and intermediate shaft fail
causing a clunking or grinding noise
and a loose or vibrating steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The front wheel bearings fail
causing a grinding or popping noise
and uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the quad steering system can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The quad steering system fails
causing the wheels to turn sideways
and the loss of control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear air suspension system can cause the loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear air suspension system fails
causing the vehicle to sag or lean to one side
and the loss of control of the vehicle.
